				</div>
				<!-- /jumpto -->
								<!-- bodycontent -->
				<div id="mw-content-text" lang="en" dir="ltr" class="mw-content-ltr"><p><b>Daniel Melnick</b> (April 21, 1932 – October 13, 2009) was an <a href="United_States" title="United States">American</a> <a href="Film_producer" title="Film producer">film producer</a> and movie studio executive who started working in Hollywood as a teenager in television and then became the producer of such films as <i><a href="All_That_Jazz_(film)" title="All That Jazz (film)">All That Jazz</a></i>, <i><a href="Altered_States" title="Altered States">Altered States</a></i> and <i><a href="Straw_Dogs_(1971_film)" title="Straw Dogs (1971 film)">Straw Dogs</a></i>. Melnick's films won more than 20 <a href="Academy_Award" title="Academy Award">Academy Awards</a> out of some 80 nominations.<sup id="cite_ref-NYTObit_1-0" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-NYTObit-1"><span>[</span>1<span>]</span></a></sup></p>
<table id="toc" class="toc">
<tr>
<td>
<div id="toctitle">
